# Walkthrough: Trump-Iran News Short Production & Git Setup

I have completed the production of your high-retention YouTube Short for the Trump-Iran crisis (dated April 14, 2026) and successfully published the codebase to GitHub.

## 🎬 Video Production Details

### 1. Dialectic News Curation
- **Research:** Curated today's headlines from Tavily and Reddit sentiment.
- **Narrative:** Formal, documentary-style narration written to match a 60-second duration.
- **Sentiment:** Integrated community skepticism and concern from Reddit into Scene 7.

### 2. Formal Layout Design
I architected a new Remotion composition `TrumpIranApr14` with a premium broadcast aesthetic:
- **Dateline Header:** "APRIL 14, 2026 • DEVELOPING" fixed top bar.
- **Kinetic Typography:** Word-by-word spring animation with active word highlighting.
- **Media Pipeline:** 
    - 7/8 real news photos fetched via Tavily.
    - 1 AI-generated fallback for Scene 6 (International Conference).
    - Authoritative ElevenLabs voiceover ("Adam").
- **Animations:** Hostile spring easing, Ken Burns zoom backgrounds, and alternating fade/slide transitions.

## 🛠️ Technical Implementation

### Repository Setup
- **Git Initialized:** Repository created and branched to `main`.
- **Remote Configured:** Linked to `https://github.com/pdtoan2811-bit/remotion`.
- **Comprehensive .gitignore:** Configured to exclude:
    - bulky media assets (voiceovers, images, rendered videos)
    - sensitive API keys (`.env`)
    - build artifacts (`node_modules`, `out/`, `dist/`)

